extendedInfo.description: CNB Mobile Banking by City National Bank allows you to bank on the go. It's free to download and offers quick access for managing your bank accounts. Check your balances, pay bills, transfer money, and locate ATMs and banking centers with just a touch. Our native app is fast, secure and free. Use your current login information to start banking today.Features:â¢Check Account Balancesâ¢Transfer funds between accountsâ¢Pay Bills**â¢Find our ATMs and Banking Centers using the GPS system provided by your Android device.****Must be an Online Banking Customer**Online customers must first setup transfer and bill pay accounts prior to using these features.***This is limited to locating our banking centers and ATMs. Please refer to your carrier for any fees that may apply.

reviews.title: I needed you!!!!!!!
reviews.comment: Works fine when it\'s NOT essential.  No advantage over browser.  Will not change orientation when phone is flipped.  CNB app, why you no flip???
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Dollar amounts
reviews.comment: One difference I notice about the app than the browser is the dollar amounts to the right of each transaction listed.. to most it doesn\'t matter, but to me its something I\'d rather use the browser to see..
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Doesn\'t recognize commands
reviews.comment: The only thing useful about this app is being able to view your account balances after logging on. When you try to select an account (if you have multiple), it only recognizes the first account listed. Also, it times out your login after only a minute or two.  Totally worthless app
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Load error
reviews.comment: Every time I try to log in it says loading error but I have no issues when going to the browser. It worked fine on my mothers apple but not at all on my Android :-(
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Works Fine
reviews.comment: No issues so far, using Samsung SII. Keep in mind that a weak signal can cause issues but that is not the apps fault
reviews.author: A Google User
